Birchwood Hotel has denied claims that it cancelled a contract with government to serve as a quarantine site for South Africans repatriated from the US. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Birchwood Hotel has denied claims that it cancelled a contract with the government to serve as a quarantine site for South Africans repatriated from the US. A group of about 200 South Africans were stranded for hours after landing at OR Tambo International Airport. Some in the group claimed they were scheduled to be quarantined at the Birchwood Hotel. READ: South Africans repatriated from US unhappy Birchwood's director Jazzman Mahlakgane said: "I think it's important that we put it on record that there is no contract." Mahlakgane said the hotel has assisted as best they can, particularly considering their location which is proximal to the airport, but has not cancelled or contravened a contract that does not exist. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.